The paper discusses the use of a biologically plausible hierarchy for face detection, alignment, and recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of neural networks and machine learning algorithms to achieve this also suggests the involvement of sub-categories such as neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on human-computer interaction, which could also place it under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
